# Cursor Rules for sh2perl Project

## Test Execution Rules
- Do not limit number of tests to run
- Fix actual timeout issues instead of adding artificial limits
- When timeouts occur, investigate the root cause in the execution framework
- Individual tests should run without arbitrary restrictions

## Code Quality Rules
- Fix compilation errors immediately
- Address type mismatches and syntax issues
- Ensure proper error handling and cleanup
- Maintain code readability and maintainability

## Performance Rules
- Optimize actual bottlenecks, don't work around them
- Profile and measure before making performance changes
- Fix infinite loops and blocking operations at their source
- Use proper timeouts and process management

## Debugging Rules
- Use debug output sparingly to avoid performance impact
- Remove or reduce verbose logging in production code
- Focus on root causes rather than symptoms

